records.addlTxt:
11:45 a.m. Defendant Chad M. Laddusire in court, in custody, with attorney Stephen D. Willett. Steven Mitchell Michlig, Asst. D.A. appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Counsel in receipt of Revocation Summary. Also calling 13CF236. Plea questionnaire filed. Willett speaks to agreement--references 03CF760 (Marathon Co. case) whereby defendant was revoked and sentenced; hence Willett filed Writ of Certiorari (CV case) originally assigned to Judge O'Melia has been intra-circuit transferred to Judge Bloom. Willett withdraws Petition for Writ. State moves to dismiss Cts. 1 & 3 in 15CF18; granted. Defendant pleads no contest to Ct. 2. Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea; waiver free & voluntary. Court finds factual basis for plea exists and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 2. Michlig/Willett/Laddusire statement to sentencing. Court statement--eligible for Challenge Incarceration & Substance Abuse Program. The court informs defendant of right to request expungement of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4). Willett w/draws Writ and will submit official paperwork.
